UNITED STATES v. DEANS. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Eighth Circuit. December 14, 1914.) No. 4169. In Error to the District Court of the United States for the Eastern District of Arkansas. W. H. Martin, U. S. Atty., of Hot Springs, Ark., for the United States.

Before SANBORN, ADAMS, and SMITH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Dismissed, without costs to either party in this court, on motion of plaintiff in error.
